    <value>As you run, you trigger the trap and several arrows tear into your skin.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_DART_DISARM_FAILED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>While disarming the trap, you lose your balance and fall onto an arrowhead, which pierces you.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_DART_DISARM_SUCCESS" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>As you bend down to examine the tile in front of you, you notice a reflection on one of the trap's arrowheads.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_DEFAULT" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You walk into the room and something doesn't seem right.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_NONE_ACTIVATED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You'll run like crazy to the other side of the room.
That's all.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_NONE_DISARM_FAILED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You worked on the trap for several minutes without any effect... Which is normal, because there was no trap!</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_NONE_DISARM_SUCCESS" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You quickly ease your doubts and realize that there is no trap.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_PIT_ACTIVATED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You feel the ground giving way beneath your feet as you run. You are knocked breathless by the impact against the edge of the hole, which you cling to with all your strength.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_PIT_DISARM_FAILED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>As soon as you start to inspect the next tile, you lose your balance and fall forward, landing on a large rock at the bottom of the hole.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_PIT_DISARM_SUCCESS" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You notice that the tile in front of you is slightly raised in one corner. You walk around the tile and continue on your way.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_POISON_ACTIVATED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>A sickening fume rises from the ground and you start coughing and crying.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_POISON_DISARM_FAILED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>While searching for the trap's trigger, you stumble upon one of the trap's gas pockets... which you accidentally puncture.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_POISON_DISARM_SUCCESS" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>During your inspection, you notice several small holes around you. You quickly hold your breath and cover your mouth and nose with a cloth.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_PRESSUREPLATE_ACTIVATED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>As soon as you start running, a flurry of rubble falls on you.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="TRAP_PRESSUREPLATE_DISARM_FAILED" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You move cautiously through the room when you feel something like sand slipping into your neck, and as soon as you look up, a large rock falls on you.</value>
